		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Need everyones help to change this<a name="33740"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 9 04 1:43 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi.  As everyone knows, with the LDoN augment system, if you place an augment on a piece of gear, and later wind up replacing that gear with an upgrade, there is no way to remove an augment without destroying it.
<br />

<br />
Since the vast majority of &quot;the best&quot; LDoN augments cost on average 1000 adventure points, by having no way to remove an augment from a piece of gear and reuse it on another piece of gear, you basically just wasted 10 - 20 hours of play time. (20 hours x 51 points per normal adventure, or 10 hours x 100-odd points per hard adventure).
<br />

<br />
As the paying customer base, we have to demand that changes are made for things that only build a time sink into the game without giving us any long term benefit.  Spending 20+ hours to purchase an LDoN aug, then upgrading that gear due to a raid/whatever....then having the augment basically rot in the bank, or be destroyed if you remove the augment of a peice of tradeable gear is a bad investment of time.
<br />

<br />
I suggest that everyone in game /FEEDBACK and suggest a change to this sytem so that augments are NOT destroyed when removed from gear with solvents, and can be reapplied to another piece of gear.  There is absolutely no reason for augments to be destroyed after we have spent countless hours to get them.
<br />

<br />
If we, as the paying customer base, dont /FEEDBACK to tell Sony that this sucks for the players, then it will never change and we will continue to suffer with the current system whereby we lose the use of items that we spent countless hours to acquire.
<br />

<br />
Thank you all for you consideration in this matter.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
