				<td colspan="2"><span>Instead of trying to get Sony to change the way augs are done(it isn't gonna happen, sorry), try to come up with a plan for what armor/weapons you have a reasonable chance at upgrading and then plan accordingly.  For example, if your guild is doing or close to RZtW then don't bother putting expensive augs in any items that you could upgrade in elementals in the next month or 2.  While it sucks that you lose augs and the time it took to get them when you upgrade, you know full well that your going to lose them upgrading so instead of demanding a change in the system to fit your needs, plan for the future.  All it means in the end is that your probably going to save up for and purchase better gear from adventures so you don't have to upgrade too often.</span></td>
