				<td colspan="2"><span>Let's look at the thing you mention about PoP, and let's look at their newest expansion, GoD:
<br />

<br />
&quot;PoK books&quot;, well, none of those go anywhere near any GoD zone. If you go from PoK, the least zones you would have to through to get to - for example - a Vxed trial, is: Everfrost, Nedaria, Natimbi, Qinimi, Barindu, compared to if you were doing anything in PoP: -&gt; PoTranq -&gt; Whatever zone you would want to go to. Furthermore the PoP travelling zone, PoTranq, is a non-fighting zone, and pretty small. In GoD: Everfrost is a bit of way, nedaria is a short stop zone, but natimbi you need to run a fair deal (with invis), Qinimi is dangerous because their might be see invis creatures (also need to use invis here), and in barindu stuff hits for Ep trash mob dmg with occasional see invis roamer (yep, also invis here). That's a sort of change, wouldn't you say?
<br />

<br />
&quot;Graveyards&quot;, most of these are gone, usually the only places you would find them is in instanced trials.
<br />

<br />
&quot;Paladins&quot;, only thing they are good at now are rezzes and bss. In a solo death you may be lucky to run across a pally that can drag you, in groups the paladin will most likely die with the cleric (group wipes are normal), in raids when wipe only FD'ers will survive (and with corpse-campers, low respawn time and tight quarters it's difficult to get up). 
<br />

<br />
&quot;Shared bank&quot;, yes, nice addition, though not a very big one. The amount of minutes saved between giving stuff to a friend and putting them in shared bank can be counted on one hand.
<br />

<br />
&quot;Fair&quot;. Hmm, what's fair? Is it fair that there are trials that take 3-6 hours to complete where if you wipe one time at any place you most likely have to start all over? Is it fair that hybrids can't tank anything noteworthy now? Is it fair that some GoD trials require 4 of the 6 group spots to be filled with specific classes, while the 2 last have &quot;recommended&quot; classes, making it almost impossible to get them completed for the last 10+ dps classes? I'm sure a player in the higher end of GoD could find a lot more things that aren't fair. And also, the augs dropping in GoD follow the same rules. That's not a single persons time, that's a raid-amount of peoples time being used to get those.
<br />

<br />
So in conclusion: no, they won't change it.</span></td>
