				<td colspan="2"><span>My whole point of comparing to GoD is that while SoE made travelling etc. easier in PoP, they changed it again in GoD, evening it out per say. And since most high end guilds have moved on to GoD with the exception of single-day raids in Time, it doesn't help much that PoP is that easy to get around.
<br />

<br />
And about the augments. It's made as it is for one thing: To be a time sink. The more time people want to use on the game, the longer it will take for them to leave. That's SoE's excuse. But since it has been made like that, then that's just the way it is, and that's the right way. It's not like it's broken or anything, it's just the way SoE intended it to be, and if it's &quot;working as intended&quot;, then it's not subject to change. Sure, it may suck that you have to destroy your precious augment when upgrading that BP or Arms slot or whatever, but that's just the way it is. 
<br />

<br />
And yes, it is fair enough. You use about (and let's be generous) an hour on an easy ldon. That's 51 points. Times ~30 that's how much points you need for - for example - a 40hp aug. Ergo SoE decided that 30 hours of work was worth a shiny 40hp aug. If that is what they think then that's fair. Let's look at an avg. EP guild. On a raid day, let's say (and let's be generous again) that they gain 10 loots on a raid. There's 60 people in the raid. They raid for 5 hours. 60*5 = 300 man hours, divided by number of loot = 30 hours per loot. These guys have worked their way through PoP to get to that spot, so it's only fair they get decent loot amount. A no drop item can only be used by one person, if the person can use something better he might as well destroy the old. That fits well with the aug thing in my opinion. 
<br />

<br />
So it all comes down to how you want to use your time really. Reusable augs is much too easy in my opinion, though fair enough if you think it's not. It just takes some consideration in where you want to put your augs. I mean, it would be stupid to put it in your crappiest gear. I for example have put augs in my stuff since GoD came out, and I haven't replaced any of that gear yet, because I put it in the items that matter.
<br />

<br />
And yes, I'm completely sure it will not change. At least not soon. Perhaps in a couple of years when there's a big exodus from EQ and GM's do everything to keep the last playerbase and do everything to please them, THEN augs might be made reusable, but not now. Definately not now.</span></td>
