				<td colspan="2"><span>There is 2 issues SoE considers before making major changes to the game:
<br />

<br />
1- Is it going to make me money?
<br />
2- Is it going to save me money?
<br />

<br />
1- Expansion offering Ports for all, Share Bank slots, zones with uber experience (compared to what was available till then. I.e: PoP), GY for corpses, uber loots, time sinks (flagging, new Tradeskill recepies), etc.
<br />

<br />
2- /petition My gear got stolen on a character transfer --&gt; Shared bank slots.
<br />
    /petition Can't find my corpse, died in water. Fell off a boat ---&gt; Ports.
<br />
    /petition My corpse rot in GoD --&gt; New Leave-Us-Alone zone for recovering corpses that rot away.
<br />
   
<br />
SoE didn't introduced Ports and Grave Yards out of kindness. It either saved them headaches, helped SoE sell more expansions, or both.
<br />

<br />
Notice how fast (or slow depending on view) they came around and introduced a &quot;Get your own rotten corpse for yourself and leave us the heck alone&quot; since they forgot to place Grave Yards in GoD, where mobs have higher DPS than PoP mobs AND they see thru rogue SoS. Kinda like with Fabled mobs when they increased the DPS but forgot level 40 mobs fell into the AE stun cathegory and Assasinate would work on them (GM_01 says out of character WTB Programmers that actually know how the game works, PST!).
<br />

<br />
Augments = more money for SoE. Enuff said.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The game began its downward spiral with PoP and we all know it. GoD is their attempt to fix it but its too late. 
<br />

<br />
People level too fast. Characters are too unproportionately uber</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Really? In what way is GoD (geared for uber characters that can withstand high DPS mobs) helping the Don't-get-too-uber-so-fast issue? Specially when consider the uber loot.
<br />

<br />
SoE had 2 choices: 
<br />

<br />
1- Keep making leveling and traveling a pain so that they didn't have to spend any time revamping the quest system, since Stein of Mogguk would still be considered uber. 
<br />

<br />
2- Sell expansion after expansion, each with yet more uber items, so quests become a myth, and everyone can focus on leveling to 65 in no time, while SoE only has to worry about keeping the level 65s in the game and collecting the monies. 
<br />

<br />
It is obvious which route SoE took.</span></td>
